value.value: A somatostatin receptor that is a translation product of the human SSTR2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A somatostatin receptor that is a translation product of the human SSTR3 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A somatostatin receptor that is a translation product of the human SSTR4 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A somatostatin receptor that is a translation product of the human SSTR5 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

An LPAR1/S1PR1-like lysophospholipid receptor that is a translation product of the human S1PR1, S1PR2, S1PR3, S1PR4, or S1PR5 genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof. The active form binds sphingosine 1-phosphate (S1P). S1P is a bioactive lysophospholipid that elicits diverse physiological effects on most types of cells and tissues.
A GPR6-like G-protein coupled receptor that is a translation product of the human GPR6 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is reported to be sphingosine 1-phosphate.
A GPR4-like G-protein coupled receptor that is a translation product of the human GPR68 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is reported to be sphingosylphosphorylcholine.

A prostanoid receptor that is a translation product of the human TBXA2R gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is thromboxane A2. This receptor is found mainly in vascular smooth muscle, where it mediates vasoconstriction, in platelets, where it mediates aggregation, and in airway smooth muscle.
A glycoprotein hormone receptor that is a translation product of the human TSHR gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is thyrotropin (thyroid-stimulating hormone).
A trace amine receptor that is a member of a subfamily comprising TAAR1, TAAR2, TAAR3P and TAAR4.
A trace amine receptor that is a translation product of the human TAAR5 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A trace amine receptor that is a member of a subfamily comprising TAAR6, TAAR7, TAAR8 and TAAR9.

A vasopressin/oxytocin receptor that is a translation product of the human AVPR1A gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is vasopressin. The receptor is expressed in vascular smooth muscle cells, hepatocytes, platelets, brain cells, and uterus cells.

A vasopressin/oxytocin receptor that is a translation product of the human AVPR1B gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is vasopressin. The receptor is expressed in cells in the anterior pituitary and throughout the brain.

A vasopressin/oxytocin receptor that is a translation product of the human AVPR2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligand is vasopressin. The receptor is expressed in kidney tubule, fetal lung, lung cancer, and liver.

A lysophospholipid (LPA) receptor that is a translation product of the human LPAR1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. It is expressed in many adult organs, including brain, heart, colon, small intestine, placenta, prostate, ovary, pancreas, testis, spleen, skeletal muscle, and kidney. There is little or no expression in liver, lung, thymus, or peripheral blood leukocytes.

A lysophospholipid (LPA) receptor that is a translation product of the human LPAR2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. It is expressed most abundantly in testis and peripheral blood leukocytes with less expression in pancreas, spleen, thymus and prostate. There is little or no expression in heart, brain, placenta, lung, liver, skeletal muscle, kidney, ovary, small intestine, or colon.

A lysophospholipid (LPA) receptor that is a translation product of the human LPAR3 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. It is most abundantly expressed in prostate, testis, pancreas, and heart, with moderate levels in lung and ovary. There is no detectable expression in brain, placenta, liver, skeletal muscle, kidney, spleen, thymus, small intestine, colon, or peripheral blood leukocytes.
A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor A that is a translation product of the mouse Mrgpra1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. RF-amide-related peptides are reported to be the preferred ligands.
A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor A that is a translation product of the mouse Mrgpra2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor A that is a translation product of the mouse Mrgpra3 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor A that is a translation product of the mouse Mrgpra4 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. RF-amide-related peptides are reported to be the preferred ligands.
A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor A that is a translation product of the mouse Mrgpra5 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor A that is a translation product of the mouse Mrgpra6 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor A that is a translation product of the mouse Mrgpra7 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor A that is a translation product of the mouse Mrgpra8 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor B that is a translation product of the mouse Mrgprb1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor B that is a translation product of the mouse Mrgprx2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

definition.value: Category=gene. Note: Although commonly designated as orthologous to human MRGPRX2, these genes are not as closely related as one would expect of true orthologs.

value.value: A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor B that is a translation product of the mouse Mrgprb8 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor X that is a translation product of the human MRGPRX1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. This receptor is specific to a subset of small dorsal root and trigeminal sensory neurons. This receptor is strongly activated by bovine adrenal medulla peptide 22 (BAM22) and related peptides.

A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor X that is a translation product of the human MRGPRX2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. This receptor has limited expression in peripheral and central nervous system, with highest levels in dorsal root ganglion. In contrast with the X1 receptor, it is activated by cortistatin-14 but only weakly by BAM22.

A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor X that is a translation product of the human MRGPRX3 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. This receptor is specific to a subset of small dorsal root and trigeminal sensory neurons.

A Mas-related G-protein coupled receptor X that is a translation product of the human MRGPRX4 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. This receptor is specific to ia subset of small dorsal root and trigeminal sensory neurons.

A lysophospholipid (S1P) receptor that is a translation product of the human S1PR1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The receptor is specifically expressed in endothelial cells, and to a lesser extent, in vascular smooth muscle cells, fibroblasts, melanocytes, and cells of epithelioid origin.
A lysophospholipid (S1P) receptor that is a translation product of the human S1PR2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A lysophospholipid (S1P) receptor that is a translation product of the human S1PR3 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. It is expressed in all tissues, but most abundantly in heart, placenta, kidney, and liver.

A lysophospholipid (S1P) receptor that is a translation product of the human S1PR4 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. This receptor is specifically expressed in fetal and adult lymphoid and hematopoietic tissue as well as in lung.

A lysophospholipid (S1P) receptor that is a translation product of the human S1PR5 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. Although widely expressed in the brain, most prominently in the corpus callosum, it is detected at a low level in most tissues.

A trace amine-associated receptor 1-4 that is a translation product of the human TAAR1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The preferred ligands of the human protein are trace amines, including beta-phenylethylamine, p-tyramine, octopamine and tryptamine. It is unresponsive to amines such as epinephrine and histamine and only partially activated by dopamine and serotonine.
A trace amine-associated receptor 1-4 that is a translation product of the human TAAR2 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A trace amine-associated receptor 1-4 that is a translation product of the human TAAR3P gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. The human protein is expressed but is probably not functional due to a frameshift mutation.
A trace amine-associated receptor 1-4 that is a translation product of the mouse Taar4 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label.value: transient receptor potential cation channel TRPM8

value.value: A transient receptor potential channel protein that is a translation product of the human TRPM8 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof. TRPM8 is a member of the subfamily M of the transient receptor potential cation channels (TRPs). In common with other TRPs, these proteins have amino- and carboxyl-terminal intracellular domains separated by a domain containing six transmembrane helices (S1-S6) in which the last two helices (S5 and S6) flank a loop, called the pore loop, which determines ion selectivity.TRPM8 forms a nonselective cation channel that is activated by cold and by menthol and other substances that produce the sensation of coolness. These channels exhibit voltage-dependance and regulation by phosphatidylinositol-4,5-bisphosphate (PIP2).
